---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Threadlines — a local workspace for coding agents"
  description="Run Claude Code and Codex in parallel threads with real source control, live usage meters, and full visibility into every task, subagent, and background run."
  canonicalPath="/preview"
  noindex
>
  <section class="pv-hero">
    <div class="pv-wrap">
      <h1 class="pv-display">Every thread leaves a line.</h1>
      <p class="pv-sub">
        Threadlines is a local desktop workspace that runs Claude&nbsp;Code and Codex in
        parallel threads — with real source control at the center, live usage meters, and
        nothing hidden. Bring the subscriptions you already pay for.
      </p>
      <div class="pv-cta-row">
        <a class="pv-cta pv-cta-primary" href="/download">Download for macOS</a>
        <a
          class="pv-cta"
          href="https://github.com/Threadlines/threadlines"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">View on GitHub</a
        >
      </div>
      <p class="pv-note">Free &amp; open source (MIT) · No account · Your code never leaves your machine</p>
      <figure class="pv-shot pv-hero-shot">
        <img
          src="/Screenshots/providers-usage.png"
          alt="Threadlines provider settings showing Codex and Claude subscriptions side by side with live 5-hour and weekly usage meters and reset countdowns"
          width="1572"
          height="832"
        />
        <figcaption>Both subscriptions, one workspace — live meters, reset countdowns, and reset credits.</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pv-section">
    <div class="pv-wrap pv-feature">
      <div class="pv-copy">
        <p class="pv-kicker">Steer, don't re-prompt</p>
        <h2>Review the agent like a pull request</h2>
        <p>
          Highlight any sentence of the agent's output — or any line of terminal output —
          and attach a note. Your annotation lands in the composer as structured context,
          quoted against exactly what you were reacting to. Course-correct mid-turn
          instead of writing paragraphs of follow-up.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="pv-media">
        <img
          src="/Screenshots/add-note.png"
          alt="Annotation popover quoting a highlighted assistant sentence with a user note reading 'this doesn't sound right'"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <img
          class="pv-media-small"
          src="/Screenshots/terminal-context.png"
          alt="Composer with attached context chips: a terminal line and a highlighted assistant quote"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pv-section">
    <div class="pv-wrap pv-feature pv-flip">
      <div class="pv-copy">
        <p class="pv-kicker">Nothing runs invisibly</p>
        <h2>Every task, subagent, and background run — visible, labeled, stoppable</h2>
        <p>
          The activity header shows what your agents are actually doing: task lists with
          live states, each subagent's goal and the model and effort it runs on, and
          background processes with a Stop button. Subagent results render as first-class
          messages in the timeline — not a collapsed spinner line.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="pv-media">
        <img
          src="/Screenshots/activity-header.png"
          alt="Thread activity popover listing current tasks, two subagents with goals and model/effort tags, and a running background process with a Stop button"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <img
          class="pv-media-small"
          src="/Screenshots/subagent-card.png"
          alt="A completed subagent's findings rendered as a first-class card in the chat timeline"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pv-section">
    <div class="pv-wrap pv-feature">
      <div class="pv-copy">
        <p class="pv-kicker">One thread, two providers</p>
        <h2>Hit a usage limit? Switch, don't stop.</h2>
        <p>
          Switch a running conversation between Claude and Codex in place — the recap and
          your working tree carry over. Usage and context live one hover away from the
          composer, so you see the wall before you hit it and keep shipping on the other
          provider when you do.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="pv-media">
        <img
          src="/Screenshots/switch-dialog.png"
          alt="Switch to Codex dialog explaining that Codex picks up a recap of the conversation and the current working tree"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <img
          class="pv-media-small"
          src="/Screenshots/context-hover.png"
          alt="Context window hover showing 39% context used plus Claude 5-hour and weekly usage meters with reset countdowns"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pv-section">
    <div class="pv-wrap pv-feature pv-flip">
      <div class="pv-copy">
        <p class="pv-kicker">Source control, built in</p>
        <h2>From agent diff to opened PR</h2>
        <p>
          A real source-control panel beside every thread: per-turn diffs, a commit graph,
          commit detail, and a one-button generate&nbsp;→&nbsp;commit&nbsp;→&nbsp;push flow
          with your hooks' output shown, not hidden. GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket, and Azure
          DevOps.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="pv-media">
        <img
          src="/Screenshots/source-actions.png"
          alt="Source control actions: generate message, commit only, commit and push, push only, plus Pull and New PR"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <img
          class="pv-media-small"
          src="/Screenshots/commit-detail.png"
          alt="Commit detail popover with SHA, author, message body, and Open on GitHub"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pv-section">
    <div class="pv-wrap">
      <p class="pv-kicker pv-center">Built to be boring</p>
      <h2 class="pv-center">Reliability is the feature</h2>
      <div class="pv-grid">
        <div class="pv-card">
          <h3>Survives restarts</h3>
          <p>Sessions resume across app and server restarts via event replay. Close the lid mid-turn; pick it back up.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pv-card">
          <h3>Fork from anywhere</h3>
          <p>Fork any message into a parallel thread — context, attachments, and working tree included.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pv-card">
          <h3>Worktrees per thread</h3>
          <p>Give each agent its own isolated checkout, or share one — your call, per thread.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pv-card">
          <h3>Always within reach</h3>
          <p>Glanceable agent status from the macOS menu bar — running threads, one click away.</p>
          <img
            class="pv-card-img"
            src="/Screenshots/menubar-tray.png"
            alt="macOS menu bar dropdown showing one running thread and quick actions"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pv-section pv-oss">
    <div class="pv-wrap pv-center">
      <p class="pv-kicker">Open source</p>
      <h2>MIT-licensed, history and all</h2>
      <p class="pv-sub">
        Threadlines began as a fork of T3 Code and grew into the safety-and-endurance
        layer for agent work: visibility, recovery, and source-control depth. The full
        git history is public — refactors, lessons, and all.
      </p>
      <p class="pv-note">github.com/Threadlines/threadlines · macOS + Windows</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .pv-wrap {
    max-width: 1040px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 24px;
  }

  .pv-hero {
    padding: 72px 0 56px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .pv-display {
    font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 3.6rem);
    line-height: 1.08;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }

  .pv-sub {
    color: var(--text-muted, #9aa3b2);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 20px auto 0;
  }

  .pv-cta-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-top: 28px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .pv-cta {
    border: 1px solid var(--border, #2a2f38);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 10px 18px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .pv-cta-primary {
    background: var(--accent-bright, #7dd3fc);
    border-color: transparent;
    color: #0b0d10;
  }

  .pv-note {
    margin-top: 16px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted, #9aa3b2);
  }

  .pv-shot img,
  .pv-media img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border: 1px solid var(--border, #2a2f38);
    border-radius: 12px;
    display: block;
  }

  .pv-hero-shot {
    max-width: 880px;
    margin: 44px auto 0;
  }

  .pv-hero-shot figcaption {
    margin-top: 12px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted, #9aa3b2);
  }

  .pv-section {
    padding: 72px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border, #232830);
  }

  .pv-feature {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.1fr;
    gap: 48px;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .pv-flip .pv-copy {
    order: 2;
  }

  .pv-kicker {
    font-family: "JetBrains Mono", ui-monospace, monospace;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent-bright, #7dd3fc);
  }

  .pv-copy h2,
  .pv-section h2 {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin: 10px 0 14px;
  }

  .pv-copy p:not(.pv-kicker) {
    color: var(--text-muted, #9aa3b2);
  }

  .pv-media {
    display: grid;
    gap: 16px;
  }

  .pv-media-small {
    max-width: 78%;
    justify-self: end;
  }

  .pv-flip .pv-media-small {
    justify-self: start;
  }

  .pv-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 20px;
    margin-top: 36px;
  }

  .pv-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--border, #232830);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 22px;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .pv-card h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .pv-card p {
    color: var(--text-muted, #9aa3b2);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .pv-card-img {
    margin-top: 14px;
    width: 100%;
    border-radius: 8px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border, #232830);
  }

  .pv-center {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .pv-oss .pv-sub {
    max-width: 620px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 820px) {
    .pv-feature {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .pv-flip .pv-copy {
      order: 0;
    }

    .pv-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 520px) {
    .pv-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
